        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 1:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 115 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Victor, or 15 miles southwest of Colorado Springs,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Colorado Springs, Fort Carson, and Stratmoor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
